      • subsumedAndResolved

        public static Clause subsumedAndResolved(Clause clause,
                                         ClauseList clauseList,
                                         ImplicationDAG implicationDAG)
        checks if the given clause is subsumed (possibly via the implication DAG).
        If not, all literals which can be resolveBackwardLiterals away (possibly via the implication DAG) are removed.
        The clause must not yet be integrated in the clause list.
        Parameters:
        clause - the clause to be checked
        clauseList - the other clauses
        implicationDAG - the implication graph
        Returns:
        null if the clause is subsumed, otherwise the possibly simplified clause

        public static int simplifyClause(Clause clause,

        simplifies a clause by means of the implication DAG.
        Example: p,q,r and p -> r: remove p
        Parameters:

        implicationDAG - the implication DAG
        Returns:
